FeedPackage.Description: Simplifies the syntax required for common interactions with SQL Databases
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes:
Completely changed how a connection string is found and used. The constructor can accept either a connection string or a connection name. If a connection name is supplied, the constructor will attempt to automatically resolve the connection name into a connection string using either the new static Dictionary or the new static search function.
Connection name/string pairs can be added to the static Dictionary via the DBManager.AddConnectionString method. A connection string search function can be set with the DBManger.SetConnectionStringSearchFunc method. These methods manipulate static fields and only need to be used once during the program's runtime.
If the constructor is not properly recognizing a connection string or connection name, the constructor can be forced to treat the parameter as one or the other via overload methods.
Full documentation website is up.
FeedPackage.Tags: SQL Database Helper
FeedPackage.Title: WS.DBAdjutor

FeedPackage.Description: Simplifies the syntax required for common interactions with SQL Databases
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: Several major changes and additions: -GetReaderField() returns object instead of string now. -GetReaderField() now has an overload method that takes an integer index and returns the field value at that index. -Added new method RecordToObject(). This can convert a record to a generic object or an object of a specified type. -Added new method AllToObjects(). This converts all records in the database results to a list of generic objects or a list of objects of a specified type. -Added new method IndexOfField(). This method operates much like an "IndexOf" on a string. It takes in a name of a field and returns the index of that field. If the field does not exist, it returns -1.
FeedPackage.Tags: SQL Database Helper
FeedPackage.Title: WS.DBAdjutor

FeedPackage.Description: Simplifies the syntax required for common interactions with SQL Databases
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes:
New method AddParams(): AddParams() takes in an object or Dictionary and assigns parameters to the SQL command. http://williamss3docs.com/DBAdjutor#AddParams
SetProcedure() and SetCommandText() have new overloads utilizing AddParams().
DBManager now has a default constructor that attempts to create a SQL Connection with the first connection string in the static Dictionary or by passing the connection string search function an empty string. http://williamss3docs.com/DBAdjutor#DBManager
FeedPackage.Tags: SQL Database Helper

FeedPackage.Description: Delivering a mobile application to multiple devices typically requires adjusting of HTML/XHTML mark-up, CSS and JavaScript. Similarly, no single combination of audio/video codecs and containers will work on all devices (not to mention frame-rates and bit-rates). For all these reasons, a Device Description Repository is required that can be queried to know whether a given device supports a given feature. An open-source database, WURFL is de-facto standard DDR in the industry. This package delivers the official WURFL ASP.NET API.
